Phrases
-------
lifecycle & lifetime : refer to when the object is
	valid/allocated/freed/invalid, who has control over that, and what
	requirements are placed on this.




Verbs
-----

create - allocate and initialize
destroy - dinitialize and deallocate

init
dinit (?)


----

put
take

get
set

give - lifecycle control passed to the called function
grab - lifecycle control is now the caller's responsibility


# I use these for reference counting. put/take may be better.
up   - 
down -

# Used by avro for reference counting
incref
decref
